en-probability-based confidence: for each instance, average the maximum next-token probability over the prompt set. Analyze Mistral-7B-Instruct, InternLM2-7B-Chat, and InternLM2-20B-Chat and show that higher decoding confidence correlates with lower PSS (greater robustness), indicating that prompt sensitivity is an external manifestation of the model’s confidence in its outputs."}]}
